body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

```verilog
module submod(output q);
wire aa = 1'b1;
assign q = aa;
endmodule

module top(output q);
wire \submod_i.aa ;
submod submod_i(.q(\submod_i.aa ));
assign q = \submod_i.aa ;
endmodule
```

Run `yosys -p "hierarchy -top top; flatten" flatten_conflict.v`

## Expected behavior

A non-conflicting wire name is generated for wire `aa` inside `submod_i`

## Actual behavior

```
ERROR: Assert `count_id(wire->name) == 0' failed in kernel/rtlil.cc:1502.
```

I should be able to fix this easily enough, but want to check how the non-conflicting name should be generated (adding a postfix, or making it a private $-name with autoidx?)

